    "recap_headline": "College of Charleston",
    "recap_text": "MT PLEASANT, S.C. \u2013\nCollege of Charleston baseball lost the series opener Friday evening to Stony Brook, 3-1, at Patriots Point.\nWith the loss, the Cougars slip to 7-10 overall and 2-2 in the CAA while Stony Brook improves to 3-12 and 2-2 in league play.\nCRITICAL POINTS AGAINST STONY BROOK:\nStony Brook jumped out to an early 1-0 lead in the first before tacking on a pair of insurance markers in the sixth.\nCharleston chipped into the lead in the home half of the sixth when\nDylan Johnson\nbrought home freshman\nJake Amman\nwith a sacrifice fly.\nFreshman\nCarter Harrington\ntossed five innings in the loss, yielding an unearned run on five hits and two walks while striking out three.\nRedshirt sophomore\nRyan Hench\ntossed two scoreless frames out of the Cougar bullpen, fanning two Seawolves.\nOF NOTE:\nCharleston is now 8-2 against Stony Brook in the all-time series.\nAmman had his fourth multi-hit game of the year with two knocks Friday.\nHench appeared in his team-best ninth ballgame out of the bullpen, lowering his ERA to 0.87 in the process.\nUP NEXT:\nCharleston faces Stony Brook in the second game of the series Saturday with a 2 p.m. first pitch at Patriots Point.\nFor complete coverage of Charleston baseball, follow us X (@CofCBaseball) and Instagram (@CofC_Baseball)."
